Commentary Text: Holder to Kohli, out Caught by Goswami!! The finger is up and Kohli was already walking - strangled down the leg-side, Holder shortened his length and got the ball to nip back into the right-hander, Kohli had the angle covered as he looked to tuck it to the on-side. The ball caught the glove and Goswami takes a sliding catch down the leg-side. Kohli was looking to be positive, but he has been sent packing early. How big is this a blow for RCB? Kohli c Goswami b Holder 6(7)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Warner, out Caught by de Villiers!! RCB review a caught-behind: It's an absolute beauty of a delivery this -- seaming in big time, following Warner's backing away and cutting him in half. Also, there's a sound as the ball goes through Warner's bat and body, and it sounds like glove. But the thigh pad is very close too. Yep, there's a spike when the ball's simultaneously under the glove and over the thigh pad. Now, now. It's all down the third umpire's bravery here. And he is a brave person .. deciding there's enough evidence to overturn this. It's a massive moment, MASSIVE. RCB know that, as their loud celebratory shreiks echo around. Warner c de Villiers b Siraj 17(17) [4s-3]
